commit.message:
Fix conversion of window_size to float breaking timedelta compatiblity

With commit 05a14608d06b06dfc589ae9c247d300b89f956b5, using a `timedelta`
as `sampling_period` in `moving_average` throws an exception when
converting `window_size` to a `float`. Multiplying by `1.` as previously
done serves the same purpose and still allows `timedelta` to be used.
removing anything having to do with python2 support
adding test to cover date parsing
